m at ease at the moment about Ukraine because because the the the this is, you know, what what what what''s going on, in media because in in the media I mean, how you can judge having, you know, some gossips, guesses, and, not not not confirmed information. I mean, what what what are these people talking about? III think, you know, the the Trump is playing very very dangerous game. And, I would say he will lose in in in in final global decision. Because he will lose because, it it will end up, on another Yalta.\n\nYou remember Yalta? Yalta Yalta Treaty Yalta Treaty? Yalta Treaty, it was on the end of, Second World War. Yalta is is actually Russian town, And there there was, like, treaty between Soviet Union at that time and, the US and, the UK. And, this was the vision of the world, The vision of everyone''s areas.\n\nRight? And it end up with this cold war and it adapt, with, kind of so socialistic communism, idea, including Poland. And nobody asked us whether we want to be, there or not. This was just, you know, like, I believe it was based on what what whether we whether the US and UK the UK, want war with Russia to, gain Poland, Czech Republic, Czechoslovakia at that time, or not, or maybe Baltic countries and take it over to and, like, rejoin them to the Western Europe. And I I mean, they they they had clear picture that they they will not be dying for Poland.\n\nRight? And this is exactly the same situation. Now now Trump is saying, I will not be dying for Ukraine. Okay. If they will give us all the resources, maybe I will consider this.\n\nRight? And this is just colonialistic colonialistic policy. Right? I mean", "paragraphs": [{"sentences": [{"text": "You know, I''m at ease at the moment about Ukraine because because the the the this is, you know, what what what what''s going on, in media because in in the media I mean, how you can judge having, you know, some gossips, guesses, and, not not not confirmed information.", "start": 111.805, "end": 141.19499}, {